Table Caption: Phases occurring in different microstructural states as determined via TEM and XRD investigations. For the 900 degC, 1 h annealing state no complimentary TEM analysis was made.

Mole fraction and composition of the system at 500 degC and 800 degC taken from Calphad simulations (TCHEA1 base). The values in the brackets are experimental data, obtained via EDX line scans, for comparison (data from 500 degC, 100 h and 800 degC, 1 h annealed specimens). Bold numbers indicate the major elements forming the phase.
Summary of mechanical properties obtained during tensile testing.
Hardness values of the individually cast phases occurring in the 800 degC, 1 h annealing treatment, before and after HPT processing.
